      "id": "RQ-0022",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Surface diagnostics persistence failures instead of swallowing write errors",
      "description": "Principles violated: F (fail fast), H (operational hygiene), J (consistency/integrity). Diagnostics writers in app presentation coordinators use `try?` for JSON encoding and file writes, silently dropping failures without telemetry or recovery state updates. Why it matters: contract diagnostics can vanish exactly when needed for investigation, while the UI appears healthy. Minimal fix: replace silent `try?` writes with explicit error handling that logs/records persistence issues and preserves an operator-visible signal. Acceptance criteria: failed diagnostics writes emit structured error telemetry and are test-covered.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "ralphmac",
        "observability",
        "fail-fast"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphMac/WorkspaceContractPresentationCoordinator.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphMac/SettingsWindowDiagnostics.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphMac/WorkspaceContractPresentationCoordinator.swift:160-167 :: persistDiagnosticsIfNeeded :: uses try? encode/createDirectory/write and drops all errors",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphMac/SettingsWindowDiagnostics.swift:248-255 :: persistDiagnosticsIfNeeded :: uses the same silent try? pattern",
        "workflow: rg -n \"try\\? data.write|try\\? FileManager.default.createDirectory\" apps/RalphMac/RalphMac --glob '*.swift' :: confirms silent persistence failures on diagnostics paths"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Refactor diagnostics persistence helpers to return/record explicit errors instead of swallowing failures.",
        "Wire persistence failures into existing diagnostics or logger channels so operators can act.",
        "Add focused tests that simulate unwritable destinations and assert recorded error signals.",
        "Verify by running `xcodebuild test -project apps/RalphMac/RalphMac.xcodeproj -scheme RalphCore -destination 'platform=macOS,arch=$(uname -m)'` and checking diagnostics-persistence failure tests."
      ],
      "notes": [],
