      "id": "RQ-0023",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Make workspace reveal timeout explicit instead of silent polling exhaustion",
      "description": "Principles violated: F (fail fast), G (least astonishment), H (operational hygiene). `scheduleWorkspaceReveal` polls up to 60 attempts with fixed sleep/yield and then silently exits with no user-visible error or telemetry if reveal never succeeds. Why it matters: workspace focus failures can become silent UX dead-ends that are difficult to diagnose. Minimal fix: replace silent exhaustion with an explicit timeout state and diagnostic event, and prefer event-driven readiness when possible. Acceptance criteria: reveal timeout is observable in diagnostics/logs and covered by deterministic tests.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "ralphmac",
        "ux",
        "operability"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceManager+Routing.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceManager+Routing.swift:115-129 :: scheduleWorkspaceReveal :: loops 60 attempts and uses fixed yield/sleep polling",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceManager+Routing.swift:131-133 :: post-loop path :: clears task without surfacing timeout/failure state",
        "workflow: rg -n \"scheduleWorkspaceReveal|workspaceRevealTask\" apps/RalphMac/RalphCore --glob '*.swift' :: confirms reveal timeout has no explicit operator-visible failure signal"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce explicit timeout outcome reporting for workspace reveal attempts.",
        "Emit structured diagnostics/log entries when reveal polling exhausts without success.",
        "Replace or minimize fixed polling with event-driven triggers where feasible.",
        "Add deterministic tests for success and timeout branches of reveal scheduling.",
        "Verify by running `xcodebuild test -project apps/RalphMac/RalphMac.xcodeproj -scheme RalphCore -destination 'platform=macOS,arch=$(uname -m)'` and asserting reveal-timeout tests pass."
      ],
