      "description": "Principles violated: E (make bugs hard to write), H (operational hygiene), J (consistency/integrity). File-size limits are documented but not enforced by current local gates, allowing oversized files to accumulate undetected. Why it matters: policy-only limits drift over time and increase refactor risk. Minimal fix: add a non-flaky local gate script/target that fails when files exceed hard limits and warns/fails on soft-limit policy as agreed. Acceptance criteria: CI/local gate fails on new hard-limit violations and reports actionable offenders.",
